  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Liberia: Promoting Worker Rights</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Solidarity Center builds the capacity of independent trade unions in Liberia to promote worker rights&#x2014;such as fair wages and safe working conditions. The project has helped workers in the agriculture, mining and railroad construction sectors, as well as domestic workers, advocate for the protection of their rights through collective bargaining. The Solidarity Center has also worked with its local partners to promote a higher minimum wage as part of a new Decent Work Bill. Liberia and Liberian workers face economic challenges and increased unemployment in the post-Ebola context, and unions are pressing for decent work and wages so that families and communities can recover.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Solidarity Center organizes educational programs and workshops to educate new union members and leaders on basic worker rights, collective bargaining procedures and ways to promote gender equality in the workplace.</narrative>
  </description>
